title: PA Major Trails
name: PA Major Trails
description: Longest continuous multi-use trails in Pennsylvania

properties.name: Mon Wharf Trail
properties.description: A $6 million project connecting the Eliza Furnace Trail with Point State Park, due to be completed in Spring of 2010. The trail will be along the river and be built with a slight tilt towards the river to allow water and mud to drain off the drail during times of flooding. Pilons will take the trail around the river side of the Fort Pitt Bridge piers. A switchback will be constructed to take the trail from the end of the Eliza Furnace Trail down to the river promenade.

properties.name: Liberty Spur
properties.description: Paved access between the trail and the Liberty Communicy Center and ballfields.

properties.name: Pine Creek Gorge Trail
properties.description: Crushed stone trail following the old rail bed through the Pine Tree Gorge, aka the Grand Canyon of Pennsylvania. -- View in full at http://ridewithgps.com/routes/18900

properties.name: Allegheny River Trail Emlenton to Oil City
properties.description: The spikes in elevation are where the trail passes through tunnels. -- View in full at http://ridewithgps.com/routes/103897
